                            <comment id="12989950" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 3 Feb 2011 03:02:58 +0000"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Currently, a scope of 0 (default) means that it won&apos;t be replicated and a scope of 1 means it&apos;s going to be. In the future, different scope could be used for routing policies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;could be &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Currently, with a scope of 0 (default) a value will not be replicated, or with a scope of 1 it will be replicated. In the future, scope values greater than 1 may be used in conjunction with more complex routing policies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


